  "doc_id": "23770",
  "text": "Haloperidol is a hydrophobic compound [CITATION_1] and can therefore freely diffuse through the plasma membrane. In our experiments, haloperidol was only able to block the channel when applied to the extracellular solution. A possible explanation for this finding is that when applied intracellularly, any haloperidol that crosses the membrane is rapidly diluted by the bulk extracellular solution before it has time to bind to its binding site.",
